            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-08 11:39:24" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to weep or wail, with emphasis upon the noise accompanying the weeping</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to weep</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to wail</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to lament</Gloss>
                <Gloss>weeping</Gloss>
                <Gloss>crying</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:04000201800020} κλαίω occurs with a so-called ‘direct object,’ for example, Ραχὴλ κλαίουσα τὰ τέκνα αὐτῆς … ὅτι οὐκ εἰσίν ‘Rachel weeps for her children … because they are all dead.’ The so-called direct object is, however, the cause of the weeping, and the so-called transitive usage of κλαίω does not alter the meaning.</Comments>
